element.definition: A sample value for this element demonstrating the type of information that would typically be found in the element.
element.comment: Examples will most commonly be present for data where it's not implicitly obvious from either the data type or value set what the values might be.  (I.e. Example values for dates or quantities would generally be unnecessary.)  If the example value is fully populated, the publication tool can generate an instance automatically.

constraint.human: All FHIR elements must have a @value or children
